# Repo Migration to Local Disk — Action Template

## Purpose
Move the working repository from a OneDrive path to a normal local-disk path so Git can be used safely across both PCs.

## Scope
Use this procedure when:
- the repo is currently inside OneDrive
- the repo needs to be stored on local disk
- the repo will be edited from more than one PC through GitHub

## Standard Paths
- Old path: `C:\Users\<username>\OneDrive\Documents\GitHub\sbxqiao-infrastructure-lab`
- New path: `C:\Repos\sbxqiao-infrastructure-lab`

## Required Outcome
- repo stored on local disk
- `.git` metadata preserved
- GitHub remote unchanged
- local repo tested and working
- old OneDrive copy removed after verification

---

## Procedure

### 1. Open the current repository

```powershell
cd "C:\Users\<username>\OneDrive\Documents\GitHub\sbxqiao-infrastructure-lab"